  "text": "Once upon a time, on the 26th of June 2026, a grand tale unfolded during the World Cup as Norway met France in a dance of skill and spirit. The air was thick with anticipation as the two travelers began their long journey across the pitch. Very early in the story, at the opening moment, Ousmane Dembélé found the magic he needed, striking a shot that carried the ball into the net to give France a 0-1 lead. The rhythm of the match shifted quickly, and moments later, a player from Norway received a yellow card as the intensity began to rise.\n\nNot long after that first spark, Ousmane Dembélé appeared once more, finding his way through the defense with another shot to make the score 0-2. Norway, however, refused to let their light fade so easily. Moments later, Thelo Aasgaard rose to the challenge, finding the back of the net with a shot of his own to bring Norway back into the fold with a score of 1-2. The balance of the tale seemed to tilt, but soon after, Ousmane Dembélé completed a quiet hat-trick of sorts, sending a third shot home to make it 1-3 for France.\n\nAs the first chapter of this adventure drew to a close, the score stood at 1-3. Much later, a player from France was shown a yellow card, adding a touch of caution to the unfolding dream. Throughout the journey, the teams sought new openings, earning a total of nine corners between them. A while later, the final flourish arrived when Désiré Doué rose high to meet the ball, scoring with a gentle header to extend the lead to 1-4. When the stars finally aligned and the journey reached its end, the story concluded with a final score of 1-4. It was a night of great movement and many memories, written under the vast, watchful sky.",
